00:30:59.180 --> 00:31:00.680
- So this notion,
I want you to hold

00:31:00.680 --> 00:31:04.160
on to this notion of
misleading correlations.

00:31:04.160 --> 00:31:06.230
What's important here
is that the project

00:31:06.230 --> 00:31:09.350
departs from a set of hypotheses
about how people interact

00:31:09.350 --> 00:31:12.140
and behave in smaller
spaces and deploys

00:31:12.140 --> 00:31:14.420
the filmic apparatus
in a structured way

00:31:14.420 --> 00:31:17.490
to test these hypotheses.

00:31:17.490 --> 00:31:20.330
This is what we might
characterize today as a small

00:31:20.330 --> 00:31:25.160
data study, which is to say
small data being characterized

00:31:25.160 --> 00:31:27.720
by their generally
limited volume,

00:31:27.720 --> 00:31:32.300
their non-continuous collection,
their narrow . variety,

00:31:32.300 --> 00:31:37.220
and usually generated to
answer very specific questions.

00:31:37.220 --> 00:31:39.470
You start with a
question about a space,

00:31:39.470 --> 00:31:42.200
what people are doing there.

00:31:42.200 --> 00:31:46.580
Now, I'd like you to compare
Whyte's apparatus with this.

00:31:46.580 --> 00:31:50.780
These are two smartphones
affixed to windows recording

00:31:50.780 --> 00:31:53.750
activity happening on a
street outside, In this case,

00:31:53.750 --> 00:31:57.620
in Manhattan as well.

00:31:57.620 --> 00:32:02.390
And this is a demo clip from
a startup called Placemeter.

00:32:02.390 --> 00:32:06.220
Placemeter is a service that
deploys crowdsource smartphones

00:32:06.220 --> 00:32:08.330
as video sensors for
monitoring activity

00:32:08.330 --> 00:32:10.670
on city sidewalks
and public spaces

00:32:10.670 --> 00:32:13.520
in cities around the world.

00:32:13.520 --> 00:32:16.460
These video feeds are
analyzed in real time

00:32:16.460 --> 00:32:18.530
based on computer
vision algorithms.

00:32:18.530 --> 00:32:21.890
And they process activity
in the video frame

00:32:21.890 --> 00:32:24.860
based on a set of predefined
classifiers established

00:32:24.860 --> 00:32:28.310
through AI and
machine-learning algorithms.

00:32:28.310 --> 00:32:31.040
Here's how a Placemeter
presents itself.

